<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-20T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="899" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d899">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/582: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-20T16:00:00-04:00">June 20,
                                    1942—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>289. Your 636, June 19, 1 p.m. General Arnold is in accord with the
                            Department’s views that the Department’s telegram no. 287, June 19, 5
                            p.m. affords adequate basis for action you suggest in your telegram
                            under reference.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>